kubelogin convert-kubeconfig -l azurecli
this command is used to convert the authentication method in your kubeconfig file - whether it has to prompt for interactive login for every time, or it has to use existing access token of the logged in user

-l azurecli - uses existing logged in user access token. if its refresh token also expired, it will prompt for login again. best for automation scripts
-l devicecode - code based auth. stores token which is separate for logged in ad user token 
-l interactive - Prompts for interactive browser login every time






